name: latoyaboydofficial
tweet: I truly believe food is medicine and have been able to help heal my mind , body and soul through a well balanced life. What can I say 🤷🏾‍♀️ I’m a Libra and we like balance. It takes an incredible amount of work to keep my world balanced but it’s worth every single second.

name: latoyaboydofficial
tweet: I’m the first person in my whole family that has chosen eastern medicine over western, I practice yoga and meditation regularly, I eat a diet high in organically home grown vegetables, fruits, and beans as well as regularly taking pre and probiotics, vitamins and water.

name: latoyaboydofficial
tweet: Also alcohol had me smoking cigarettes like a chimney. For the record, I quit tobacco 6 years ago cold turkey. No patches or gum. I quit alcohol and cigs at the same time🙌🏾 Never picked the bacco back up since. I’m really proud of myself.

name: latoyaboydofficial
tweet: Just because your family history is just that, history, doesn’t mean you have to go down the same path. You can change your family history starting with you. Break the fucking cycle. I may consume cannabis in ridiculously high volumes, but it’s not alcohol. 🤷🏾‍♀️ I’ll take it.

name: latoyaboydofficial
tweet: So I will say this. Have your fun, just don’t let it cost you your health. Thankfully I didn’t go down the same path as those in my family. I come from a family of alcoholics so the fact I stopped before it actually damaged me beyond reverse, is progress.

name: latoyaboydofficial
tweet: When I did drink, I was lazy AF. I wasn’t a crying or angry drunk either. I was the fun drinker- not the party girl. I didn’t do dumb shit completely..... but I just didn’t like being hungover or being bloated. I gained so much weight from drinking, it was gross.

name: latoyaboydofficial
tweet: It used to be hard to admit these harsh realities until I got into my 30’s and realized there was so much more I missed. Like running tack. I also realized I drank the most when I was depressed... you guys I spent my teens until, 36 trying to drink the pain away.

name: latoyaboydofficial
tweet: I never thought I drank a lot until I realized when I did, I binged drank. So going days on end without a drink and then having 12 in one sitting is not the right answer, no matter if you think it’s not a big deal. It adds up over time.

name: latoyaboydofficial
tweet: It was fun while it lasted but I literally cannot drink alcohol again. It will kill me. Beside I love weed wayyyyy more. pic.twitter.com/tKmhxWdyi4
